e.com/books?id=WcXHRVYzV4MC |year=2009 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-1-136-51751-8 |ref={{sfnref|Panigrahi, Jammu and Kashmir, the Cold War and the West|2009}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Paul |first=T. V. |title=Asymmetric Conflicts: War Initiation by Weaker Powers |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Sc0YjTKul5MC |year=1994 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-46621-9 |ref={{sfnref|Paul, Asymmetric Conflicts|1994}}}}\n* {{citation |first=Balraj |last=Puri |authorlink=Balraj Puri |title=The Question of Accession |journal=Epilogue |volume=4 |number=11 |pp=4\u20136 |date=November 2010 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TMxJzb7N_8wC&pg=PA4 |ref={{sfnref|Puri, The Question of Accession|2010}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Puri |first=Luv |authorlink=Luv Puri |title=Across the Line of Control: Inside Azad Kashmir |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ItY3BAAAQBAJ |date=2013 |publisher=Columbia University Press |isbn=978-0-231-80084-6 |ref={{sfnref|Puri, Across the Line of Control|2013}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Raghavan |first=Srinath |title=War and Peace in Modern India |date=2010 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EbtBJb1bsHUC |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |isbn=978-1-137-00737-7 |ref={{sfnref|Raghavan, War and Peace in Modern India|2010}}}}\n* {{cite book |first=Mridu |last=Rai |authorlink=Mridu Rai| title=Hindu Rulers, Muslim Subjects: Islam, Rights, and the History of Kashmir |publisher=C. Hurst & Co |year=2004 |isbn=978-1850656616 |ref={{sfnref|Mridu Rai, Hindu Rulers, Muslim Subjects|2004}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Rizvi |first=Gowher |authorlink=Gowher Rizvi |chapter=India, Pakistan and the Kashmir Problem |editor=Raju G. C. Thomas |title=Perspectives on Kashmir: the roots of conflict in South Asia |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xrPtAAAAMAAJ |year=1992 |publisher=Westview Press |isbn=978-0-8133-8343-9 |ref={{sfnref|Rizvi, India, Pakistan and the Kashmir Problem|1992}} |url=https://archive.org/details/perspectivesonka00thom }}\n* {{citati