{"title_page": "The Voice UK (series 8)", "text_new": "{{short description|Eighth series of The Voice UK}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox reality talent competition\n| name          = The Voice UK\n| season        = 8\n| first_aired   = {{Start date|2019|01|05|df=yes}}\n| last_aired    = {{End date|2019|04|06|df=yes}}\n| coaches = {{Plainlist|\n* [[will.i.am]]\n* [[Jennifer Hudson]]\n* [[Tom Jones (singer)|Sir Tom Jones]]\n* [[Olly Murs]] \n* [[Simon Cowell]] (Guest Judge)\n}}\n| host          = [[Emma Willis]]<br>[[Ant & Dec]]\n| cohost        = [[AJ Odudu]] (ITV Hub & [[YouTube]])\n| broadcaster   = {{Plainlist|\n* [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]\n* [[ITV Hub]] (''The V Room'')\n* [[YouTube]] (''The V Room'')\n}}\n| winner-name   = [[Molly Hocking]]\n| winner-origin =  [[Cornwall]], [[England]]\n| winner-genre  =[[Soul music|Soul]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| winner-song   = [[I'll Never Love Again]]\n| winner-mentor  = [[Olly Murs]]\n| runner-name   = [[Deana Walmsley]]\n| british       = yes\n| last          = The Voice UK (series 7)\n| year          = 2019\n| next          = The Voice UK (series 9)\n}}\n'''''[[The Voice UK]]''''' is a British television music competition to find new singing talent. The '''eighth series''' began airing on 5 January 2019 and concluded on 6 April 2019, presented by [[Emma Willis]] on [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]. [[will.i.am]], [[Jennifer Hudson]], [[Tom Jones (singer)|Sir Tom Jones]] and [[Olly Murs]] returned for their eighth, third, seventh and second series, respectively. The series is the third and final series under the new three-year contract confirmed by ITV in November 2015.\n\n==Coaches and presenters==\nOn 1 November 2018, it was announced that [[Vick Hope]] (last series' backstage reporter and ''The V Room'' host) would be replaced by [[AJ Odudu]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.itv.com/thevoice/aj-odudu-is-the-new-backstage-reporter-for-the-voice-uk|title=AJ Odudu is the new Backstage Reporter for The Voice UK|website=www.itv.com|access-date=2019-03-14}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March 2019, the guest mentors for the knockout round were announced to be: [[James Arthur]] to help Sir Tom Jones, [[Nicole Scherzinger]] to help will.i.am, [[Olly Alexander]] (of [[Years & Years]]) to help Jennifer Hudson and [[Anne-Marie (singer)|Anne-Marie]] to help Olly Murs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-03-07/the-voice-2019-guest-judges-coaches-nicole-scherzinger-james-arthur-olly-alexander-anne-marie/|title=The Voice 2019 guest mentors revealed|website=Radio Times|language=en|access-date=2019-03-14}}</ref>\n\n{{multiple image\n| header = Series 8 coaches\n| total_width = 400\n| direction = horizontal\n| image4 = Olly Murs-9859.jpg\n| width4 = 2700\n| height4 = 3500\n| alt4 = \n| caption4 = [[Olly Murs]]\n| image2 = Jennifer-Hudson 2012-01-17 Barnes-Noble Chicago photoby Adam-Bielawski.jpg\n| width2 = 1045\n| height2 = 1500\n| alt2 = \n| caption2 = [[Jennifer Hudson]]\n| image3 = Tom Jones concert.jpg\n| width3 = 1880\n| height3 = 2816\n| alt3 = \n| caption3 = [[Tom Jones (singer)|Sir Tom Jones]]\n| image1 = Will.i.am in 2012.jpg\n| width1 = 1300\n| height1 = 1950\n| alt1 = 1300\n| caption1 = [[will.i.am]]\n| align = \n| width = \n}}\n\n== Teams ==\nColour key:\n\n* {{Color box|#FFF44F|border=darkgray}} Winner\n* {{Color box|#B0E0E6|border=darkgray}} Runner-up\n* {{Color box|#B2EC5D|border=darkgray}} Third place\n* {{Color box|#FBCEB1|border=darkgray}} Fourth place \n* {{Color box|#E8CCD7|border=darkgray}} Eliminated in the Semi-Final\n* {{Color box|#BFFFC0|border=darkgray}} Eliminated in the Knockouts\n* {{Color box|#FFFDD0|border=darkgray}} Artist was stolen by another coach at the Battles\n* {{Color box|pink|border=darkgray}} Eliminated in the Battles\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:09%;\" |Coach\n! colspan=\"6\" scope=\"col\" |Top 40 Artists\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"row\" |will.i.am\n| colspan=\"6\" styl