asons that will.i.am does not have an artist represented in the final.  This is also the first time in the show's history that only two coaches are represented in the final.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; width:75%;\"\n|+\n|-\n! style=\"width:05%;\" | Order\n! style=\"width:15%;\" | Coach\n! style=\"width:20%;\" | Artist\n! style=\"width:20%;\" | Song\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Result\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 1\n| will.i.am\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |Emmanuel Smith\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |\"[[Giant (Calvin Harris and Rag'n'Bone Man song)|Giant]]\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:pink;\" |Eliminated\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 2\n| Jennifer Hudson\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |Nicole Dennis\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |\"[[Dream On (Aerosmith song)|Dream On]]\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 3\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Sir Tom Jones\n| Deana Walmsley\n| \"[[Autumn Leaves (1945 song)|Autumn Leaves]]\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | Advanced\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 4\n| Bethzienna Williams\n| \"[[You Don't Own Me]]\"\n|- \n! scope=\"col\" `| 5\n| Olly Murs\n| Jimmy Balito\n| \"[[Fix You]]\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 6\n| Jennifer Hudson\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |Moya\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |\"[[I Will Wait]]\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background:pink;\" |Eliminated\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 7\n| will.i.am\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |NXTGEN\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |\"Embrace\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 8\n| Sir Tom Jones\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |Cedric Neal\n| style=\"background:pink;\" |\"[[High Hopes (Panic! at the Disco song)|High Hopes]]\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 9\n| Olly Murs\n| Molly Hocking\n| \"[[I'll Never Love Again]]\"\n| style=\"background:lightgreen;\" | Advanced\n|}\n\n====Week 2: Final (6 April)====\n*Musical guest: [[Ruti Olajugbagbe|Ruti]] (\"Racing Cars\")\n\nGroup performance: The Voice UK coaches \u2013 \"[[Gimme Some Lovin']]\"\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-a