tyle=\"width:15%;\"| Contestant\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20%;\"| Week 1\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20%;\"| Week 2\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:17%;\"| Round 1\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:17%;\"| Round 2\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Blessing Chitapa\n| \n|\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Brooke Scullion\n| \n|\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Doug Sure\n| \n|\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Gevanni Hutton\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Jonny Brooks\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Jordan Phillips\n| \n| \n|\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Lois Moodie\n| \n| \n|\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Lucy Calcines\n| \n|\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" | Trinity-Leigh Cooper\n| \n|\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n====Week 1: Semi-final (TBA)====\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; width:75%;\"\n|+\n|-\n! style=\"width:05%;\" | Order\n! style=\"width:15%;\" | Coach\n! style=\"width:20%;\" | Artist\n! style=\"width:20%;\" | Song\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Result\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 1\n| \n| \n| \n| \n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 2\n| \n| \n| \n|\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 3\n| \n| \n| \n| \n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 4\n|\n| \n| \n|\n|- \n! scope=\"col\" `| 5\n| \n| \n| \n|\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 6\n| \n| \n| \n| \n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 7\n| \n| \n| \n|\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 8\n| \n| \n| \n|\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | 9\n| \n| \n| \n| \n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.itv.com/thevoice/ Official website]\n\n{{The Voice UK}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Voice UK (series 9)}}\n\n[[Category:The Voice UK]]\n[[Category:2020 British television seasons]]\n[[Category:Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on television]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ninth series of The Voice UK}}\n{{Infobox reality talent competition\n| name = The Voice UK\n| season = 9\n| num_episodes = 12<!-- Value is incremented when new episodes air. See template documentation for more info. -->\n| british = yes\n| host = [[Emma Willis]]\n| coaches = {{Plainlist|\n* [[will.i.am]]\n* [[Meghan Trainor]]\n* [[Tom Jones (singer)|Sir Tom Jones]]\n* [[Olly Murs]]\n}}\n| cohost = \n| broadcaster = [[ITV (TV channel)|ITV]]\n| year = 2020\n| first_aired = 4 January 2020\n| last_aired = present\n| last = The Voice UK (series 8)\n| next = \n| winner-name = \n| winner-genre = \n| winner-mentor = \n| winner-origin = \n| winner-song = \n| runner-name =\n}}\n''[[The Voice UK]]'' is a British television music competition to find new singing talent. The ninth series began airing on 4 January 2020, presented by [[Emma Willis]] on [[ITV (TV channel)|ITV]]. [[will.i.am]], [[Tom Jones (singer)|Sir Tom Jones]] and [[Olly Murs]] returned for their ninth, eighth and third series, respectively, as coaches. [[Jennifer Hudson]] did not return as a coach for this series and was replaced by singer-songwriter [[Meghan Trainor]]. A promotional trailer was released on 6 December 2019.\n\nDue to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], the semi-final and final of the competition have been postponed. It was originally to air on 28 March and 4 April but set to air on a later date.\n\n== Coaches and presenters ==\n{{multiple image\n| header = Series 9 coaches\n| total_width = 400\n| direction = horizontal\n| image4 = Olly Murs-9859.jpg\n| width4 = 2700\n| height4 = 3500\n| alt4 = \n| caption4 = [[Olly Murs]]\n| image2 = 150426 Meghan Trainor.jpg\n| width2 = 1045\n| height2 = 1500\n| alt2 = \n| caption2 = [[Meghan Trainor]]\n| image3 = Sir Tom Jones at The Queen's Birthday Party (cropped).jpg\n| width3 = 4000\n| height3 = 4000\n| alt3 = \n| caption3 = [[Tom Jones (singer)|Sir Tom Jones]]\n| image1 = Will.i.am in 2018.jpg\n| width1 = 1500\n| height1 = 2000\n| alt1 = 1300\n| caption1 = [[will.i.am]]\n}}\nOn 26 September 2019, it was confirmed that [[will.i.am]], [[Tom Jones (singer)|Sir Tom Jones]] and [[Olly Murs]] would return to the show as coaches for their ninth, eighth and third series, respectively.<ref name=\"coaches\">{{cite news |last1=Pearce |first1=Tilly |title=Meghan Trainor confirmed to replace Jennifer Hudson as judge on The Voice UK |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/09/26/meghan-trainor-confirmed-to-replace-jennifer-hudson-as-judge-on-the-voice-uk-10816213/ |accessdate=18 October 2019 |work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=26 September 2019}}</ref> They are joined by new coach [[Meghan Trainor]], an American [[Grammy Award]] winning singer-songwriter, who replaces former coach [[Jennifer Hudson]]. Hudson opted not to return for her fourth series due to filming commitments in the US, which prevented her from returning.<ref name=\"coaches\"/> Trainor expressed her excitement at joining the coaching team and commented, \"It's a dream come true and I can't wait to sit in the chair with my own button and listen to some incredible new talent!\"<ref name=\"Trainor\">{{cite news |title=Meghan Trainor to replace Jennifer Hudson on The Voice UK as Dreamgirls star quits show |url=https://www.heart.co.uk/showbiz/tv-movies/the-voice/meghan-trainor-jennier-hudson-the-voice-uk/ |accessdate=18 October 2019 |work=[[Heart (radio network)|Heart]] |date=27 September 2019}}</ref> Alongside the coaches, the return of presenter [[Emma Willis]] was announced; she was excited by Trainor's casting.<ref name=\"Trainor\"/>\n\nTrainor later spoke about joining the coaching panel, admitting that she found it \"intimidating\" and felt \"insecure\" about what the contestants would think about her, believing she was not as well established in comparison to the rest of the panel.<ref name=\"YorkPress\">{{cite news |title=Meghan Trainor explains why joining The Voice UK was 'intimidating' |url=https://www.yorkpress.co.uk/leisure/showbiz/18124003.meghan-trainor-explains-joining-voice-uk-intimidating/ |accessdate=27 December 2019 |work=[[The Press (York)|The Press]] |date=27 December 2019}}</ref> She added that she was nervous about replacing Hudson and asked her for advice on how to approach the show.<ref name=\"YorkPress\"/> will.i.am thought it was hard for Trainor to settle into the position because Hudson was well loved on the show, but believed that Trainor would be liked by the audience too.<ref name=\"YorkPress\"/> Murs agreed and described Trainor as \"a very powerful woman, she's got this great energy about her, she's fun.\"<ref name=\"YorkPress\"/>\n\n== Development ==\nFilming for this series commenced on 14 October 2019 at [[Dock10 (television facility)|Dock 10 studios]] with the taping of the blind auditions.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tonks |first1=Andrea |title=Tom Jones: The Voice UK star seen with new coach Meghan Trainor after Jennifer Hudson exit |url=https://www.express.co.uk/celebrity-news/1190954/Tom-Jones-The-Voice-UK-2019-Meghan-Trainor-Jennifer-Hudson-pictures-news |accessdate=18 October 2019 |work=[[Daily Express]] |date=15 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nA promotional trailer for the series was released on 6 December 2019, featuring the coaching panel.<ref name=\"trailer\">{{cite news |last1=Edwards |first1=Chris |title=The Voice UK trailer gives coaches Olly Murs and will.i.am unexpected new looks |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/a30152940/the-voice-uk-olly-murs-william-trailer-new-looks/ |accessdate=27 December 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |date=6 December 2019}}</ref> The series premiered on [[ITV (TV channel)|ITV]] on 4 January 2020 in the 20:30 timeslot.<ref name=\"YorkPress\"/>\n\nOn 18 March, it was announced by ITV that the live semi-final which was scheduled for Saturday 28 March, would be postponed until later in the year due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|coronavirus  pandemic]].<ref name=Revamp>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51931050 |title=Coronavirus: BBC and ITV revamp broadcast plans amid outbreak |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=18 March 2020 |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Teams ==\nColour key:\n\n* {{Color box|#FFF44F|border=darkgray}} Winner\n* {{Color box|#B0E0E6|border=darkgray}} Runner-up\n* {{Color bo